{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhases"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Moon","identifiers":["doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Moon","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonPhase","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/MoonQuarter","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Libration","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/LunarNode","doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/NodeKind"],"anchor":"Moon"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/Moon","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" type provides comprehensive lunar calculations including phase angles, illumination, quarter searches, libration data, and node crossings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Phase Angle","anchor":"Phase-Angle","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The phase angle indicates the Moon’s position in its cycle:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","print(\"Phase angle: \\(angle)°\")","\/\/ 0° = New Moon, 90° = First Quarter, 180° = Full, 270° = Third Quarter"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Phase Names and Emoji","anchor":"Phase-Names-and-Emoji","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convert angles to human-readable descriptions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","","print(Moon.phaseName(for: angle))  \/\/ \"Waxing Gibbous\"","print(Moon.emoji(for: angle))      \/\/ \"🌔\""]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The eight phase names:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New Moon (🌑)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Waxing Crescent (🌒)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First Quarter (🌓)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Waxing Gibbous (🌔)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Full Moon (🌕)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Waning Gibbous (🌖)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Third Quarter (🌗)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Waning Crescent (🌘)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","text":"Illumination","anchor":"Illumination","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Calculate the fraction of the Moon that’s lit:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let angle = try Moon.phaseAngle(at: .now)","let illumination = Moon.illumination(for: angle)","print(\"Moon is \\(Int(illumination * 100))% illuminated\")"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Finding Quarter Phases","anchor":"Finding-Quarter-Phases","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Search for a Specific Phase","anchor":"Search-for-a-Specific-Phase","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["\/\/ Next full moon (nil if none occurs within the search window)","if let fullMoon = try Moon.searchPhase(.full, after: .now) {","    print(\"Next full moon: \\(fullMoon)\")","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Get the Next Quarter","anchor":"Get-the-Next-Quarter","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let quarter = try Moon.searchQuarter(after: .now)","print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.phase.name) at \\(quarter.time)\")"]},{"type":"heading","text":"All Quarters in a Date Range","anchor":"All-Quarters-in-a-Date-Range","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let start = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 1, day: 1)","let end = AstroTime(year: 2025, month: 2, day: 1)","","let quarters = try Moon.quarters(from: start, to: end)","for quarter in quarters {","    print(\"\\(quarter.phase.emoji) \\(quarter.time)\")","}"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Lunar Position","anchor":"Lunar-Position","level":2},{"type":"heading","text":"Ecliptic Coordinates","anchor":"Ecliptic-Coordinates","level":3},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let position = try Moon.ecliptic(at: .now)","print(\"Longitude: \\(position.longitude)°\")","print(\"Latitude: \\(position.latitude)°\")","print(\"Distance: \\(position.distance) AU\")"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Moon State (Position and Velocity)","anchor":"Moon-State-Position-and-Velocity","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get the Moon’s complete state vector including velocity:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let state = try Moon.geoState(at: .now)","","\/\/ Position in AU","print(\"Distance: \\(state.position.magnitude) AU\")","","\/\/ Velocity in AU\/day","let speed = sqrt(","    state.velocity.x * state.velocity.x +","    state.velocity.y * state.velocity.y +","    state.velocity.z * state.velocity.z",")","print(\"Speed: \\(speed) AU\/day\")"]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"geoState(at:)"},{"text":" for velocity calculations instead of differencing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"ecliptic longitude positions, which gives inaccurate results.","type":"text"}]}],"style":"tip","name":"Tip","type":"aside"},{"type":"heading","text":"Using CelestialBody","anchor":"Using-CelestialBody","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Moon is also available as a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/AstronomyKit\/documentation\/AstronomyKit\/CelestialBody","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let horizon = try CelestialBody.moon.horizon(at: .now, from: observer)","let equatorial = try CelestialBody.moon.equatorial(at: .now)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Libration","anchor":"Libration","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Libration is the Moon’s apparent wobble that lets us see slightly more than 50% of its surface:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let lib = Moon.libration(at: .now)","","\/\/ Sub-Earth point (what's at the center of the visible disc)","print(\"Latitude: \\(lib.subEarthLatitude)°\")","print(\"Longitude: \\(lib.subEarthLongitude)°\")","","\/\/ Distance and apparent size","print(\"Distance: \\(Int(lib.distanceKM)) km\")","print(\"Apparent diameter: \\(lib.apparentDiameter)°\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Interpret libration values:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive latitude: More of the north polar region is visible"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Positive longitude: More of the Moon’s east limb is visible"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Lunar-Nodes","text":"Lunar Nodes","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The nodes are where the Moon’s orbit crosses the ecliptic plane:"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Find next node crossing","let node = try Moon.searchNode(after: .now)","print(\"\\(node.kind.symbol) \\(node.kind.name) at \\(node.time)\")","\/\/ Output: \"☊ Ascending Node at 2025-01-15...\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Node-Types","text":"Node Types","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ascending (☊)"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Moon crosses from south to north of the ecliptic"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragra